                        <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>01.</h4>
                            <p>In a small bowl, mix soy sauce, water, garlic, honey and cornstarch. Set aside.
</p>
                        </div>
                        <!-- Single Preparation Step -->
                        <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>02.</h4>
                            <p>Slice the tenderloin in half lengthwise to make 2 pieces, then slice into smaller slices approximately 1/4 inch thick. Set aside.
</p>
                        </div>
                        <!-- Single Preparation Step -->
                        <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>03.</h4>
                            <p>Heat a large skillet over medium high heat. Add oil to lightly coat the pan. Add pork pieces and cook, stirring, until the pork is almost completely cooked, about 4 minutes.
</p>
                        </div>
                        <!-- Single Preparation Step -->
                        <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>04.</h4>
                            <p> Add frozen veggies to the pan and cook over medium high heat until thawed and no longer frozen. 
</p>
                        </div>
						 <div class="single-preparation-step d-flex">
                            <h4>05.</h4>
                            <p>Increase the heat to high. Add the stir fry sauce to the pan and cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture begins to boil. Reduce heat to low and cook for 1-2 minutes. Remove from heat. Sauce will thicken and coat the stir fry as it cools. 
 </p>
                        </div>
						
